_An Irish Zen koan by Graham Priest:_

-->What is the sound of one pint of Guinness?

----

_A haiku in the form of a limerick by Adrian Henri:_

-->In the town of the grey granite tower
-->With the smell of the balsam in flower
-->On that final June day
-->When we both went away
-->You turned as the clock struck the hour.

_A limerick in the form of a haiku by Jason Grossman:_

-->There was an old man
-->Who came in Spring to Japan
-->That silly old man

_A random haiku by Someone in MATH1007:_

-->Haikus are awesome
-->They do not have to make sense
-->Refrigerator.

